Today was the longest day
of my life.

1037
01:00:32,962 --> 01:00:36,227
Well, aside from my stomachache,
I thought it felt pretty good.

1038
01:00:36,633 --> 01:00:39,124
Definitely worth a journal entry,
ya know?

1039
01:00:45,174 --> 01:00:46,732
What are you doin'?

1040
01:00:47,210 --> 01:00:49,201
I'm writin' in my journal.

1041
01:00:49,512 --> 01:00:51,309
But it's not even your journal.

1042
01:00:51,414 --> 01:00:53,382
Why don't you worry
about going to sleep,

1043
01:00:53,483 --> 01:00:55,883
and I'll worry about writing
in my journal, okay?

1044
01:01:07,633 --> 01:01:10,261
That's it.
It's over.

1045
01:01:10,369 --> 01:01:12,234
So much for my legacy.

1046
01:01:18,544 --> 01:01:20,307
They've come for us!

1047
01:01:21,513 --> 01:01:23,743
You boys like a drink of water?

1048
01:01:24,016 --> 01:01:25,347
You got any yoohoo?

1049
01:01:25,451 --> 01:01:27,749
Milk?
Some skim milk?

1050
01:01:27,853 --> 01:01:29,718
Who are you guys anyway?

1051
01:01:29,822 --> 01:01:34,418
- We're missionaries.
- From the booklet...

1052
01:01:34,727 --> 01:01:38,823
Do you know the purpose of life?
'Cuz I do.

1053
01:01:39,732 --> 01:01:41,290
I definitely do.

1054
01:01:43,502 --> 01:01:46,960
Sorry to put you boys out,
but we're on official business.

1055
01:01:47,072 --> 01:01:48,630
Thanks for the ride.

1056
01:01:48,741 --> 01:01:52,108
Call the number on this card.
They'll send you a free video.

1057
01:01:52,544 --> 01:01:55,172
Let me know if you find out
the meaning of life.

1058
01:01:55,281 --> 01:01:56,839
Oh, but, we, we have!

1059
01:01:56,949 --> 01:01:58,007
That is... the point.

1060
01:01:58,117 --> 01:01:59,607
It's in the book.

1061
01:01:59,718 --> 01:02:00,776
I tried to tell...

1062
01:02:00,886 --> 01:02:01,818
Okay. Bye.

1063
01:02:01,921 --> 01:02:03,786
Ah... civilization.

1064
01:02:03,889 --> 01:02:05,015
So dramatic.

1065
01:02:05,124 --> 01:02:07,820
You make it sound like
we were gone for a month.

1066
01:02:07,927 --> 01:02:09,792
I'm starving.
Let's find a restaurant.

1067
01:02:09,895 --> 01:02:11,294
We still got some Twinkies.

1068
01:02:12,231 --> 01:02:15,098
Come on, delicious, tasty,
golden, delicious...

1069
01:02:15,200 --> 01:02:16,599
Okay, you're gonna
make me vomit.

1070
01:02:16,702 --> 01:02:19,603
...and it's got the filling
with the creaminess.

1071
01:02:19,705 --> 01:02:21,798
Come on, one Twinkie?

1072
01:02:28,614 --> 01:02:31,242
He is pretty cute.

1073
01:02:31,350 --> 01:02:32,783
In fact, they both are.

1074
01:02:32,885 --> 01:02:35,012
They are missionaries.

1075
01:02:35,621 --> 01:02:37,782
I've seen the way
you've been lookin' at him.

1076
01:02:37,890 --> 01:02:39,221
Don't be ridiculous.

1077
01:02:42,061 --> 01:02:44,859
What would you do
if he wasn't a missionary?

1078
01:02:46,365 --> 01:02:48,390
I'm not playin' your little game.

1079
01:02:52,071 --> 01:02:54,733
So, when are you going
to start dating again?

1080
01:02:54,840 --> 01:02:57,502
You know, I know four priests
who'd go out with you.

1081
01:02:57,609 --> 01:02:59,270
Stop this.

1082
01:02:59,378 --> 01:03:02,006
What?
It's true.

1083
01:03:02,114 --> 01:03:05,277
Come on, let me set you up
so you can have fun.

1084
01:03:05,384 --> 01:03:07,545
I'm not having
this conversation.

1085
01:03:07,653 --> 01:03:10,451
So, how many priests
are in this town?

1086
01:03:10,556 --> 01:03:13,389
About 15, but only 5 are active.

1087
01:03:13,492 --> 01:03:17,656
Eighteen teachers
and 21 deacons.

1088
01:03:17,763 --> 01:03:19,321
You're allowed to date priests?

1089
01:03:19,431 --> 01:03:21,524
They can date priests
but not deacons.

1090
01:03:21,633 --> 01:03:24,568
Teachers aren't supposed to,
but some do.

1091
01:03:24,670 --> 01:03:27,400
Ick, teachers are so immature.

1092
01:03:27,506 --> 01:03:32,136
Not as bad as some
of the elders I know.

1093
01:03:32,244 --> 01:03:34,109
I think I'm getting a headache.

1094
01:03:34,213 --> 01:03:36,181
With only one week
to election day,

1095
01:03:36,281 --> 01:03:38,841
polls are suggesting that
Senator Boxwell is a shoe-in.

1096
01:03:38,951 --> 01:03:40,578
The man can do no wrong.

1097
01:03:40,686 --> 01:03:41,516
It's come down...

1098
01:03:41,620 --> 01:03:43,315
Will you turn that up?

1099
01:03:43,422 --> 01:03:47,290
You guys aren't supposed
to watch TV.

1100
01:03:47,393 --> 01:03:49,054
Senator, what do you attribute

1101
01:03:49,161 --> 01:03:51,721
your last term's
incredible success to?

1102
01:03:51,830 --> 01:03:53,320
Well, aside from hard work,

1103
01:03:53,432 --> 01:03:57,198
I'd have to say a very loving
and supportive family.

1104
01:03:57,302 --> 01:03:59,429
Your daughters are adorable.

1105
01:03:59,538 --> 01:04:01,802
It's nice to see
such a strong family man

1106
01:04:01,907 --> 01:04:04,273
representing our great state.

1107
01:04:04,376 --> 01:04:05,468
Thank you very much.

1108
01:04:05,577 --> 01:04:08,045
And regardless of what happens
next week, Christine,

1109
01:04:08,147 --> 01:04:11,310
I know I'll always have
a loving and supportive family.

1110
01:04:11,417 --> 01:04:13,009
There you have it Bob,
Roy Boxwell,

1111
01:04:13,118 --> 01:04:15,086
a great senator and a great...

1112
01:04:18,791 --> 01:04:20,520
You all right, man?

1113
01:04:41,380 --> 01:04:43,712
Yeah, can I get Roy Boxwell,
please?

1114
01:04:45,017 --> 01:04:46,678
This is Justin.

1115
01:04:47,052 --> 01:04:48,747
Look, he knows who I am.

1116
01:04:52,991 --> 01:04:55,858
Yes, well put him through.

1117
01:04:57,696 --> 01:04:59,095
Justin, where are you?

1118
01:04:59,198 --> 01:05:02,565
I am in the middle of the desert,
right where you sent me.

1119
01:05:02,668 --> 01:05:03,965
What do you want... money?

1120
01:05:04,069 --> 01:05:07,368
I don't need your money.

1121
01:05:07,473 --> 01:05:09,100
Then what?

1122
01:05:09,208 --> 01:05:12,439
I saw your little TV interview today.

1123
01:05:12,544 --> 01:05:14,978
You're quite the family man
these days.

1124
01:05:15,080 --> 01:05:17,412
Justin, tell me where you
are so we can talk.

1125
01:05:17,516 --> 01:05:19,313
Nice try, Senator.

1126
01:05:19,418 --> 01:05:21,545
Justin, let me send someone for you.

1127
01:05:21,653 --> 01:05:23,245
You wanna send someone to get me?

1128
01:05:23,355 --> 01:05:24,947
Yes, I do.

1129
01:05:25,057 --> 01:05:26,752
Let me have your pen.

1130
01:05:28,560 --> 01:05:30,653
See you around, Roy.

1131
01:05:30,762 --> 01:05:33,162
Justin!
Justin!

1132
01:05:36,101 --> 01:05:38,331
What?

1133
01:05:38,437 --> 01:05:41,838
Look, I'm on the last week
of my reelection campaign,

1134
01:05:41,940 --> 01:05:43,601
don't screw this up.

1135
01:05:56,655 --> 01:05:59,055
What was that all about?

1136
01:06:06,865 --> 01:06:07,593
Hello?

1137
01:06:07,699 --> 01:06:09,599
Yes, is Justin there?

1138
01:06:09,701 --> 01:06:11,726
No, nobody named Justin.

1139
01:06:11,837 --> 01:06:15,068
Tell me, where is this phone located?

1140
01:06:15,174 --> 01:06:17,642
It's a pay phone inside
the New Harmony Diner.

1141
01:06:17,743 --> 01:06:18,869
New Harmony?

1142
01:06:18,977 --> 01:06:20,171
Who is this?

1143
01:06:20,279 --> 01:06:22,509
All right, thank you very much.

1144
01:06:22,614 --> 01:06:25,105
Get General Wilkins
on the phone for me.

1145
01:06:25,617 --> 01:06:26,914
How did you know?

1146
01:06:27,019 --> 01:06:30,614
Half the camp knew you were
related to some politician.

1147
01:06:30,722 --> 01:06:31,882
Now I know which one.

1148
01:06:31,990 --> 01:06:36,723
Not a word, okay?
Please?

1149
01:06:36,828 --> 01:06:38,796
Why can't we get this in the open?

1150
01:06:38,897 --> 01:06:40,159
It's not a good idea.

1151
01:06:40,265 --> 01:06:41,664
What's the worst that can happen?

1152
01:06:41,767 --> 01:06:44,702
To him?
To him, probably nothin'!

1153
01:06:44,803 --> 01:06:47,363
He would claim he was helping
out some troubled kid

1154
01:06:47,472 --> 01:06:49,099
and walk away smelling like a rose.

1155
01:06:49,208 --> 01:06:50,368
Then why'd you call him?

1156
01:06:50,475 --> 01:06:52,568
I couldn't just sit back

1157
01:06:52,678 --> 01:06:55,169
and let him get away with all
that family-man crap, okay?

1158
01:06:55,280 --> 01:06:56,247
He's a liar.

1159
01:06:56,348 --> 01:06:58,839
Face it, man!
Okay, your dad's a politician.

1160
01:06:58,951 --> 01:07:02,387
He is not the ideal family man,
but so what, who cares?

1161
01:07:02,487 --> 01:07:04,352
You got your own life, man!

1162
01:07:05,791 --> 01:07:08,851
Justin, I mean that.
You got your own life, dude.

1163
01:07:08,961 --> 01:07:11,589
So then let's go.

1164
01:07:11,697 --> 01:07:14,461
It's you and me just like we planned.

1165
01:07:19,771 --> 01:07:23,639
Actually, I'm sorta likin'
what's happening around here, man.

1166
01:07:23,742 --> 01:07:26,336
Huh... you, you mean
this missionary stuff?

1167
01:07:26,445 --> 01:07:27,707
Yeah.

1168
01:07:28,046 --> 01:07:29,206
Yeah!

1169
01:07:29,314 --> 01:07:33,876
I mean, it's not my style,
but I just like it-- it's fun.

1170
01:07:33,986 --> 01:07:35,681
I guess I just like helping people,

1171
01:07:35,787 --> 01:07:36,981
you know?

1172
01:07:37,089 --> 01:07:38,716
Hey, you listen to me.

1173
01:07:38,824 --> 01:07:40,485
The fuse is lit, all right?

1174
01:07:40,592 --> 01:07:42,253
The real elders are coming.

1175
01:07:42,361 --> 01:07:43,521
I know, I know.

1176
01:07:43,629 --> 01:07:45,494
So let's go while we still can!

1177
01:07:45,597 --> 01:07:46,564
Come on!

1178
01:07:46,665 --> 01:07:49,657
Something's just telling me
we shouldn't.

1179
01:07:49,768 --> 01:07:52,498
Ha, ha, it's the cafe food talking',
all right?

1180
01:07:52,604 --> 01:07:55,869
I can't deny the way I feel, man.

1181
01:07:55,974 --> 01:08:02,243
We cannot stay here forever,
okay, Elder Talbot?

1182
01:08:02,347 --> 01:08:05,009
We'll leave when the time is right.

1183
01:08:07,953 --> 01:08:10,080
I swear!

1184
01:08:10,188 --> 01:08:14,625
I swear on the Bible
and the Book of Mormon.

1185
01:08:14,726 --> 01:08:17,217
You're so stupid.

1186
01:08:17,329 --> 01:08:18,660
Atta baby.

1187
01:08:20,365 --> 01:08:20,990
All right?

1188
01:08:21,099 --> 01:08:22,066
It's not our money.

1189
01:08:22,167 --> 01:08:23,759
Don't make me take it from you.

1190
01:08:23,869 --> 01:08:26,463
Try to take it from me
and I'll put you down.

1191
01:08:26,571 --> 01:08:27,663
I'm gonna count to three.

1192
01:08:27,773 --> 01:08:29,866
I'm warning you,
I am a trained martial artist.

1193
01:08:29,975 --> 01:08:31,237
One.

1194
01:08:35,480 --> 01:08:36,777
Two.

1195
01:08:39,084 --> 01:08:41,052
Two and a half.

1196
01:08:41,153 --> 01:08:44,145
All right buddy, snake eyes, okay?

1197
01:08:44,256 --> 01:08:46,121
Watch out for him, he's everywhere.

1198
01:08:46,224 --> 01:08:46,781
Ow.

1199
01:08:46,892 --> 01:08:47,916
Give it to me.

1200
01:08:48,727 --> 01:08:49,386
Right now.

1201
01:08:49,494 --> 01:08:53,521
Oh, man.
That really stings.

1202
01:08:53,632 --> 01:08:58,126
All right girls,
with the backpack you've got a deal.

1203
01:08:58,236 --> 01:09:01,000
Hey, I'm gonna get a hemorrhoid
from a seat that small.

1204
01:09:01,707 --> 01:09:04,301
They're going to be great;
the baskets are very nice.

1205
01:09:04,409 --> 01:09:07,003
And check this out...

1206
01:09:07,112 --> 01:09:09,444
Would you just hush up.

1207
01:09:09,548 --> 01:09:10,446
Bubbles!

1208
01:09:10,549 --> 01:09:12,517
Ahh, you know their names.
Perfect.

1209
01:09:12,617 --> 01:09:14,915
Yeah, but I'm not telling you
the other two.

1210
01:09:15,020 --> 01:09:15,952
So, ha!

1211
01:09:21,426 --> 01:09:23,553
Gentlemen, what are you thinking?

1212
01:09:23,662 --> 01:09:26,187
I mean you just leave the keys
in the ignition?

1213
01:09:26,298 --> 01:09:27,788
It's not real safe.

1214
01:09:27,899 --> 01:09:29,958
You never know
who's gonna pick 'em up.

1215
01:09:31,570 --> 01:09:34,505
I suppose you're not going
to give us back our keys?

1216
01:09:37,275 --> 01:09:40,210
Uh... no.

1217
01:09:48,887 --> 01:09:49,979
What's this all about?

1218
01:09:50,088 --> 01:09:52,579
This is about who stays
and who goes.

1219
01:09:52,924 --> 01:09:53,948
Oh, I get it.

1220
01:09:54,059 --> 01:09:56,391
This town isn't big enough
for both of us.

1221
01:09:56,495 --> 01:09:58,588
Showdown at the lemonade corral,
huh?

1222
01:09:58,697 --> 01:10:01,962
Come on, Daren, let's do this.

1223
01:10:02,067 --> 01:10:04,058
You boys get
two minutes' head start.

1224
01:10:04,169 --> 01:10:05,966
Last man without paint wins.

1225
01:10:06,071 --> 01:10:07,095
Wins what?

1226
01:10:07,205 --> 01:10:09,400
We win... you got ten minutes
to pack your stuff.

1227
01:10:09,508 --> 01:10:10,805
You're gonna run us outta town?

1228
01:10:10,909 --> 01:10:12,137
Yep... just like we did

1229
01:10:12,244 --> 01:10:14,940
with the last two dork missionaries.

1230
01:10:15,046 --> 01:10:18,447
If we win, we get our keys back.

1231
01:10:18,550 --> 01:10:19,983
We stay, and all you boys

1232
01:10:20,085 --> 01:10:23,213
have to attend church
for the next six months.

1233
01:10:24,790 --> 01:10:27,156
Come on, Daren,
let's get on with it.

1234
01:10:27,259 --> 01:10:30,490
Two minutes starts-- now.

1235
01:10:32,030 --> 01:10:32,962
Stay.

1236
01:10:33,064 --> 01:10:35,498
Elder Johnson,
spirit's telling me to move,

1237
01:10:35,600 --> 01:10:36,897
let's move, so let's move.

1238
01:10:37,002 --> 01:10:38,594
I ain't runnin' anymore.

1239
01:10:38,703 --> 01:10:40,466
What are you doin', man?

1240
01:10:42,107 --> 01:10:45,042
Elder Johnson,
what would Jesus do, okay?

1241
01:10:45,143 --> 01:10:45,632
Let's go.

1242
01:10:45,744 --> 01:10:46,802
Jesus?

1243
01:10:46,912 --> 01:10:49,472
Jesus wouldn't run
from a bunch of rednecks.

1244
01:10:49,581 --> 01:10:50,548
Heh.

1245
01:10:50,649 --> 01:10:52,879
Looks like these Bible boys
know how to play.

1246
01:10:54,019 --> 01:10:55,782
I've gotta work in a half hour.

1247
01:10:55,887 --> 01:10:57,855
Shut up, Dale.

1248
01:10:57,956 --> 01:10:59,856
Just me and you, huh,
preacher boy?

1249
01:10:59,958 --> 01:11:00,856
You first.

1250
01:11:00,959 --> 01:11:03,427
I'll take the rest of your crew, huh?

1251
01:11:06,298 --> 01:11:08,596
Come on, man,
you gotta make this interesting.

1252
01:11:08,700 --> 01:11:10,861
Come on, let's just go.
Let's just go.

1253
01:11:54,079 --> 01:11:56,946
I guess I'll see you boys
at church on Sunday.

1254
01:12:09,561 --> 01:12:12,553
# Sometimes you gotta take
one step back #

1255
01:12:12,664 --> 01:12:16,498
# To go two steps
forward #

1256
01:12:16,601 --> 01:12:19,570
# Sometimes you gotta
stop believing #

1257
01:12:19,671 --> 01:12:22,834
# And find the faith #

1258
01:12:22,941 --> 01:12:26,104
# What's done is done #

1259
01:12:26,211 --> 01:12:29,510
# Tomorrow has just begun... #

1260
01:12:29,614 --> 01:12:33,573
Hey, check this out.

1261
01:12:33,685 --> 01:12:35,243
Are you pushing me
off the road?

1262
01:12:35,353 --> 01:12:37,253
Hands up, come on.

1263
01:12:37,355 --> 01:12:40,153
Hey, nice day for a ride,
huh guys?

1264
01:12:40,258 --> 01:12:41,555
What the fetch!

1265
01:12:41,660 --> 01:12:43,491
Those are the guys
who stole our car!

1266
01:12:43,595 --> 01:12:44,527
Catch 'em.

1267
01:12:44,629 --> 01:12:46,290
Come on.
Pump.

1268
01:12:46,398 --> 01:12:47,126
Pump!

1269
01:12:47,232 --> 01:12:48,062
I'm tryin'.

1270
01:12:48,166 --> 01:12:49,190
You're on my wheel.

1271
01:12:49,301 --> 01:12:50,199
Lance Armstrong!

1272
01:12:50,302 --> 01:12:52,497
I can't do it, Elder.
I'm walking.

1273
01:13:03,481 --> 01:13:06,575
Elders, what's going on?

1274
01:13:08,253 --> 01:13:09,083
You know what, Bishop?

1275
01:13:09,187 --> 01:13:10,085
We just saw the...

1276
01:13:10,188 --> 01:13:11,621
Burnett Brothers.

1277
01:13:11,856 --> 01:13:13,824
Listen, I have a surprise
for you two.

1278
01:13:13,925 --> 01:13:16,257
Can you get yourselves
cleaned up?

1279
01:13:17,329 --> 01:13:19,160
We are sort of in a hurry.

1280
01:13:19,264 --> 01:13:23,166
Yeah, our laundry smells
really bad, sir.

1281
01:13:23,268 --> 01:13:24,394
Please.

1282
01:13:24,502 --> 01:13:26,732
It's only going to take
a couple of minutes.

1283
01:13:31,076 --> 01:13:32,509
Come on.

1284
01:13:46,091 --> 01:13:48,082
THREE BOGIES!

1285
01:13:48,193 --> 01:13:49,387
Hey, Bishop.

1286
01:13:49,494 --> 01:13:50,620
Hello, Sarah, how are you?

1287
01:13:50,729 --> 01:13:51,718
Good.
Hey, Elder.

1288
01:13:51,830 --> 01:13:53,127
Hey, Sarah.

1289
01:13:53,231 --> 01:13:55,495
Elders, come on over.

1290
01:13:55,600 --> 01:13:57,568
Oh, hey, you're out!

1291
01:13:57,669 --> 01:13:59,432
They couldn't find a thing.

1292
01:13:59,537 --> 01:14:00,629
Ha ha!

1293
01:14:00,739 --> 01:14:03,765
So, here I am.
I hate hospital food.

1294
01:14:03,875 --> 01:14:05,433
Looks like you're making up for it.

1295
01:14:05,944 --> 01:14:07,741
Please, sit down.

1296
01:14:10,515 --> 01:14:13,609
Elders, I know that things
have been kinda crazy

1297
01:14:13,718 --> 01:14:15,549
these past few days.

1298
01:14:15,654 --> 01:14:17,087
Yeah, they have.

1299
01:14:19,190 --> 01:14:21,454
I'm thinking about getting baptized.

1300
01:14:23,094 --> 01:14:26,120
Less than three days
and already you have a convert.

1301
01:14:27,265 --> 01:14:30,029
Are you sure we're not
rushing things a little bit?

1302
01:14:31,269 --> 01:14:32,759
What do you mean, Elder?

1303
01:14:35,573 --> 01:14:37,768
How do you know Brother Steedman
is thinking clearly?

1304
01:14:37,876 --> 01:14:39,571
He just got out of the hospital.

1305
01:14:39,678 --> 01:14:41,009
Reggie?

1306
01:14:41,112 --> 01:14:47,642
Well, I know it sounds crazy,
but, um, this feels right.

1307
01:14:50,388 --> 01:14:53,050
You Elders know what
that's like, don't you?

1308
01:14:53,925 --> 01:14:56,621
Yes, we do.

1309
01:14:56,728 --> 01:14:59,788
And I'd like you to be the one
to baptize me, Elder Johnson.

1310
01:15:01,132 --> 01:15:02,463
Me?

1311
01:15:03,702 --> 01:15:05,829
Would you do me the honor?

1312
01:15:12,077 --> 01:15:14,409
Can both of you excuse us
for a minute,

1313
01:15:14,512 --> 01:15:19,711
while I speak to Elder Johnson,
I mean Elder Talbot, in private?

1314
01:15:24,155 --> 01:15:26,589
Hey you!
Not so fast!

1315
01:15:30,395 --> 01:15:31,987
I know who you are.

1316
01:15:32,530 --> 01:15:33,656
What's going on?

1317
01:15:33,765 --> 01:15:36,029
We played pool together
two nights ago.

1318
01:15:37,335 --> 01:15:39,200
You must have me confused
with someone else.

1319
01:15:39,304 --> 01:15:40,236
I don't think so.

1320
01:15:40,338 --> 01:15:42,863
Daren, leave him alone.

1321
01:15:43,174 --> 01:15:45,836
He wore a cowboy hat, sunglasses.

1322
01:15:45,944 --> 01:15:48,572
Said he was passing through town
like a bad burrito?

1323
01:15:48,680 --> 01:15:50,011
There is obviously some mistake.

1324
01:15:50,115 --> 01:15:51,480
Missionaries don't play pool.

1325
01:15:51,583 --> 01:15:53,244
He ordered beer.

1326
01:15:53,351 --> 01:15:55,410
Yeah, well, missionaries
don't drink either.

1327
01:15:55,520 --> 01:15:56,748
You did.

1328
01:15:56,855 --> 01:15:58,220
You're a liar.

1329
01:15:58,323 --> 01:15:59,517
Shut up, Sarah.

1330
01:15:59,624 --> 01:16:03,287
Easy pal, or I'm going to be
introducing you to the ground.

1331
01:16:03,394 --> 01:16:04,326
Daren, stop!

1332
01:16:04,429 --> 01:16:05,987
So, shut up!

1333
01:16:07,265 --> 01:16:09,096
Back off, cowboy, all right?

1334
01:16:11,703 --> 01:16:12,897
Daren, stop it!

1335
01:16:13,004 --> 01:16:17,737
Easy boys, let's end this now.

1336
01:16:17,842 --> 01:16:21,369
I never forget a face,
especially an ugly one.

1337
01:16:21,479 --> 01:16:23,504
His name is Elder Johnson,
all right?

1338
01:16:27,819 --> 01:16:29,309
Look, we are missionaries, okay?

1339
01:16:29,420 --> 01:16:31,115
We don't want any trouble.

1340
01:16:31,222 --> 01:16:32,883
It's okay, Tyler.

1341
01:16:33,458 --> 01:16:35,255
You know, you're right.

1342
01:16:35,660 --> 01:16:39,619
I did play pool with you
the other night,

1343
01:16:39,731 --> 01:16:41,756
and I cleaned you out.

1344
01:16:42,167 --> 01:16:43,532
I told you.

1345
01:16:43,735 --> 01:16:44,793
See, I knew it!

1346
01:16:45,069 --> 01:16:47,594
He's been lying
to all of us.

1347
01:16:47,705 --> 01:16:49,468
He's a hustler.

1348
01:16:55,914 --> 01:16:59,907
My name is Tyler,
and we're not missionaries.

1349
01:17:02,387 --> 01:17:05,982
We are from a correctional camp
in the Mojave Desert.

1350
01:17:06,991 --> 01:17:08,117
The pickup we stole

1351
01:17:08,226 --> 01:17:10,990
broke down in the middle
of the desert.

1352
01:17:11,095 --> 01:17:13,928
So, we grabbed the first car
that came along.

1353
01:17:15,900 --> 01:17:17,094
I'm sorry.

1354
01:17:17,202 --> 01:17:19,193
I allowed you into my home.

1355
01:17:21,606 --> 01:17:23,233
I trusted you.

1356
01:17:27,745 --> 01:17:29,804
Is this true?

1357
01:17:34,385 --> 01:17:36,444
Yeah.

1358
01:17:38,790 --> 01:17:40,587
Shame on you.

1359
01:17:46,197 --> 01:17:48,097
- Sarah.
- Don't.

1360
01:17:53,338 --> 01:17:54,635
Senator.

1361
01:17:56,941 --> 01:17:58,135
I'm Bishop Hollister.

1362
01:17:58,243 --> 01:17:59,175
Bishop, it's a pleasure.

1363
01:17:59,277 --> 01:18:01,142
What are you doin' here?

1364
01:18:01,246 --> 01:18:02,838
I've come to get you, Justin.

1365
01:18:02,947 --> 01:18:05,006
I'm not going anywhere with you.

1366
01:18:05,116 --> 01:18:05,912
Justin.

1367
01:18:06,017 --> 01:18:07,917
Wait.

1368
01:18:08,019 --> 01:18:09,486
I'll take over from here, Senator.

1369
01:18:09,587 --> 01:18:11,714
Oh, it's all right, General.

1370
01:18:11,823 --> 01:18:14,121
I had a long talk
with Bishop Hollister here.

1371
01:18:14,225 --> 01:18:16,625
He's told me everything
that has been going on, Justin.

1372
01:18:19,597 --> 01:18:20,996
You know, in all the years

1373
01:18:21,099 --> 01:18:23,829
of military schools
and outreach programs,

1374
01:18:23,935 --> 01:18:26,631
I've never had such praise
for my son.

1375
01:18:33,544 --> 01:18:39,210
Did he mention car thief,
impostor, liar?

1376
01:18:40,385 --> 01:18:44,082
Like father, like son.
Right, Dad?

1377
01:18:44,188 --> 01:18:48,318
You lie to your people,
and I lie to mine.

1378
01:18:48,426 --> 01:18:49,415
Give him a chance.

1379
01:18:49,527 --> 01:18:50,994
He had his chance.

1380
01:18:52,463 --> 01:18:53,691
We're done.

1381
01:18:53,798 --> 01:18:55,732
Look, Justin,

1382
01:18:55,833 --> 01:18:58,427
come back with me, please?

1383
01:18:58,536 --> 01:19:00,504
We'll start over, I promise you.

1384
01:19:00,605 --> 01:19:02,869
Ah, that's nice.

1385
01:19:02,974 --> 01:19:07,536
Senator Boxwell welcomes back
his prodigal son.

1386
01:19:07,645 --> 01:19:09,408
That'll make quite the headline.

1387
01:19:09,514 --> 01:19:11,675
This isn't about headlines,
and you know that.

1388
01:19:11,783 --> 01:19:13,375
This is about you and me.

1389
01:19:14,886 --> 01:19:18,583
You're about 15 years late...
Dad.

1390
01:19:20,992 --> 01:19:24,223
It's better late than never.

1391
01:19:24,329 --> 01:19:27,355
I'd give a million dollars
to meet my father.

1392
01:19:33,438 --> 01:19:36,737
Hey, everybody,
we're the new missionaries!

1393
01:19:44,949 --> 01:19:47,042
What's your name, Elder?

1394
01:19:47,552 --> 01:19:49,918
- I'm Elder Talbot.
- And I'm Elder Johnson.

1395
01:19:50,021 --> 01:19:53,548
Sorry it took us so long,
but these flippin'...

1396
01:19:53,958 --> 01:19:55,425
These fetchin'...

1397
01:19:56,561 --> 01:19:58,153
We sorta got sidetracked.

1398
01:19:59,464 --> 01:20:02,524
I feel we already know you, Elders.

1399
01:20:03,401 --> 01:20:05,198
You guys look hungry.

1400
01:20:05,737 --> 01:20:06,863
Told you I lost weight.

1401
01:20:06,971 --> 01:20:08,996
It just didn't look like it to me.

1402
01:20:10,708 --> 01:20:14,474
Hey, that is a really nice tie!

1403
01:20:14,579 --> 01:20:16,046
Oh, thank you.

1404
01:20:16,147 --> 01:20:17,808
Does this belong to you?

1405
01:20:23,021 --> 01:20:25,455
Thank you, Elder Talbot.

1406
01:20:27,625 --> 01:20:31,493
And, uh, this belongs to you.

1407
01:20:35,900 --> 01:20:39,768
I'm sorry.

1408
01:20:41,539 --> 01:20:42,972
Uh, my name is Tyler,

1409
01:20:44,075 --> 01:20:47,704
and most people know me
as "Elder Talbot."

1410
01:21:02,427 --> 01:21:05,021
All right.
Get in the pipe!

1411
01:21:19,577 --> 01:21:27,279
# Who wants to go,
who wants to go to heaven? #

1412
01:21:27,385 --> 01:21:32,982
# Who needs to ask
or reason why? #

1413
01:21:34,625 --> 01:21:35,717
Come on!
Move it!

1414
01:21:35,827 --> 01:21:39,957
# Who wants to go,
who wants to go to heaven? ##

1415
01:21:41,332 --> 01:21:43,323
Remember the first time
we came here together?

1416
01:21:43,434 --> 01:21:45,231
Yeah, I do.

1417
01:21:45,336 --> 01:21:47,201
Almost two years ago.

1418
01:21:47,638 --> 01:21:49,196
Has it been that long?

1419
01:21:53,344 --> 01:21:55,938
Just a little somethin'
from all of us at the diner.

1420
01:22:02,887 --> 01:22:05,151
These are my travel books
from years ago.

1421
01:22:05,256 --> 01:22:06,484
You broke into my house?

1422
01:22:06,591 --> 01:22:09,560
Hello! I have a key!
Open it up.

1423
01:22:09,660 --> 01:22:13,562
# Who wants to go,
who wants to go to heaven? #

1424
01:22:13,664 --> 01:22:21,332
# Who needs to ask
or reason why? #

1425
01:22:21,439 --> 01:22:22,872
# Who wants to burn... ##

1426
01:22:22,974 --> 01:22:24,202
I can't accept this.

1427
01:22:24,308 --> 01:22:26,469
Well, it's not transferable
and nonrefundable.

1428
01:22:26,577 --> 01:22:27,407
Danielle!

1429
01:22:27,512 --> 01:22:29,173
Sarah!

1430
01:22:29,280 --> 01:22:31,407
You gotta stop thinkin'
about everyone else for once,

1431
01:22:31,516 --> 01:22:34,314
especially what's his name.

1432
01:22:34,418 --> 01:22:37,512
It would mean a lot
to all of us if you went.

1433
01:22:41,559 --> 01:22:43,789
I'm going to New York City.

1434
01:22:43,895 --> 01:22:45,260
It's pretty cool, huh?

1435
01:22:45,363 --> 01:22:51,097
# ...A chance to die,
to be reborn #

1436
01:22:53,104 --> 01:23:00,840
# With just one kiss...
just one kiss... #

1437
01:23:00,945 --> 01:23:06,941
# With just one kiss
and you're mine #

1438
01:23:07,051 --> 01:23:09,884
# Hold on #

1439
01:23:09,987 --> 01:23:11,648
Put 'em up.

1440
01:23:15,993 --> 01:23:18,860
Now, fill it back up.

1441
01:23:20,031 --> 01:23:27,460
# I lay my dream
down before you #

1442
01:23:27,572 --> 01:23:35,240
# A splendid tapestry,
it's so old #

1443
01:23:35,346 --> 01:23:42,980
# But tread so carefully,
for there is danger #

1444
01:23:43,087 --> 01:23:51,119
# You might just trample
on my dream #

1445
01:23:51,229 --> 01:23:58,533
# To never,
ever be forgiven #

1446
01:23:58,636 --> 01:24:06,634
# To never,
ever wonder why #

1447
01:24:06,744 --> 01:24:10,305
# With just one kiss #

1448
01:24:10,414 --> 01:24:14,407
# A feat such as this #

1449
01:24:14,518 --> 01:24:19,353
# With just one
and you're mine ##

1450
01:24:20,091 --> 01:24:22,889
Steal water?
You earn a day in the pipe.

1451
01:24:22,994 --> 01:24:24,461
Any questions?

1452
01:24:24,562 --> 01:24:25,756
Speak up, son.

1453
01:24:25,863 --> 01:24:28,127
My um, my cousin told me

1454
01:24:28,232 --> 01:24:30,029
that two boys
died this past summer.

1455
01:24:30,134 --> 01:24:34,332
Earlier today we had 12 graduates,
a real success.

1456
01:24:34,438 --> 01:24:36,497
He said their eyes
were plucked out by vultures,

1457
01:24:36,607 --> 01:24:39,098
and their skin
was dried out like leather.

1458
01:24:39,210 --> 01:24:42,976
Well, let's just stick to the
mission at hand, shall we?

1459
01:24:43,581 --> 01:24:45,242
All right.

1460
01:24:47,852 --> 01:24:49,251
Can I come in?

1461
01:24:49,353 --> 01:24:51,048
You already did.

1462
01:24:52,890 --> 01:24:54,380
So, congratulations, man!

1463
01:24:54,492 --> 01:24:55,789
We did it!
We're done.

1464
01:24:55,893 --> 01:24:56,518
This is it.

1465
01:24:56,627 --> 01:24:58,185
Yeah, you too.

1466
01:24:58,296 --> 01:24:59,126
You all packed?

1467
01:24:59,230 --> 01:25:01,221
Uh, gettin' there.

1468
01:25:01,332 --> 01:25:06,861
So, have you heard from her?

1469
01:25:06,971 --> 01:25:08,336
No.

1470
01:25:10,875 --> 01:25:12,502
It's no big deal.

1471
01:25:12,610 --> 01:25:13,770
Huh... liar.

1472
01:25:13,878 --> 01:25:15,072
- No!
- Okay.

1473
01:25:15,179 --> 01:25:16,043
I'm okay.

1474
01:25:16,147 --> 01:25:17,045
Okay, ha ha.

1475
01:25:17,148 --> 01:25:19,013
I'm just gonna work
all summer... and...

1476
01:25:19,116 --> 01:25:21,050
forget all about her.

1477
01:25:22,520 --> 01:25:24,249
Sure.

1478
01:25:26,023 --> 01:25:27,888
What about you?

1479
01:25:27,992 --> 01:25:30,085
I haven't picked
a school yet.

1480
01:25:31,395 --> 01:25:34,626
Guess I'll wait and see where
the wind blows me, ya know?

1481
01:25:37,234 --> 01:25:39,498
Man, I'm so done with this place.

1482
01:25:41,972 --> 01:25:43,769
Yeah.

1483
01:25:52,450 --> 01:25:55,351
You're gonna be all right, man?

1484
01:25:55,453 --> 01:25:57,216
Elder.

1485
01:26:06,497 --> 01:26:11,264
I'm going to see
the Riveter, hoo hooo!

1486
01:26:11,369 --> 01:26:13,462
Yaaaa hahaha!

1487
01:26:13,571 --> 01:26:15,766
Wheee!

1488
01:26:22,313 --> 01:26:24,747
Okay, man, this is your space.

1489
01:26:24,849 --> 01:26:27,943
Don't you take
no crap from nobody!

1490
01:26:28,052 --> 01:26:29,280
Okay.

1491
01:26:29,920 --> 01:26:31,478
ORDER UP!

1492
01:26:38,596 --> 01:26:41,064
You are gettin' pretty fast
back there.

1493
01:26:41,799 --> 01:26:43,630
Bring it on, baby.

1494
01:26:43,968 --> 01:26:45,731
If you don't get back to work!

1495
01:26:45,836 --> 01:26:47,599
You see me awful busy in here.

1496
01:27:29,947 --> 01:27:34,611
I don't think
we've been properly introduced.

1497
01:27:35,986 --> 01:27:39,854
I'm Sarah,
and I own the diner in town.

1498
01:27:45,529 --> 01:27:46,962
I'm Justin.

1499
01:27:47,064 --> 01:27:53,628
I, uh, shovel... stuff,
all day long.

1500
01:27:54,972 --> 01:27:57,839
I understand
you give riding lessons.

1501
01:27:58,909 --> 01:28:01,002
Oh, Brother Steedman
gives the lessons.

1502
01:28:01,111 --> 01:28:04,512
I just sort of
make him look good.

1503
01:28:05,349 --> 01:28:07,579
Is he around?

1504
01:28:07,685 --> 01:28:11,280
No, he uh, he won't be back
until tomorrow.

1505
01:28:15,292 --> 01:28:19,251
Come here, I have something
I want to show you.

1506
01:28:19,363 --> 01:28:20,921
Look, Sarah,

1507
01:28:26,203 --> 01:28:28,364
I came back
to make things right.

1508
01:28:29,507 --> 01:28:31,771
And I don't expect
anything from you.

1509
01:28:36,413 --> 01:28:38,381
I know.

1510
01:28:40,951 --> 01:28:44,352
You, uh, might want to watch
where you're steppin'.

1511
01:28:51,695 --> 01:28:53,754
I'm glad you came back.

1512
01:28:55,199 --> 01:28:57,064
Now, come on!

1513
01:29:01,705 --> 01:29:04,333
I figured if you're
gonna be around awhile,

1514
01:29:04,441 --> 01:29:07,171
you oughta be properly introduced
to New Harmony.

1515
01:29:07,278 --> 01:29:10,543
Well, it puts a new perspective
on things, doesn't it?

1516
01:29:10,648 --> 01:29:11,615
It really does.

1517
01:29:11,715 --> 01:29:13,307
How about a barrel roll?

1518
01:29:13,417 --> 01:29:14,714
Wooohooo!

1519
01:29:14,818 --> 01:29:15,546
Whoa!

1520
01:29:15,653 --> 01:29:17,780
Load the barrel...
hahahahaha!

1521
01:29:17,888 --> 01:29:19,150
Whoa.

1522
01:29:19,256 --> 01:29:19,915
Help!

1523
01:29:20,024 --> 01:29:20,752
Sister Cutbank, stop!

1524
01:29:20,858 --> 01:29:22,052
Look what you're doing.

1525
01:29:22,159 --> 01:29:24,184
You two ever been to Australia?

1526
01:29:24,295 --> 01:29:26,422
No, Sister Cutbank, we haven't.

1527
01:29:27,998 --> 01:29:31,399
Why don't we just go
down under right now,

1528
01:29:31,502 --> 01:29:33,436
just the three of us?

1529
01:29:33,537 --> 01:29:37,337
It can't be more than
a couple of thousand miles.

1530
01:29:37,441 --> 01:29:39,306
We're a little low on fuel.

1531
01:29:39,410 --> 01:29:42,072
Ah, good point.

1532
01:29:42,179 --> 01:29:45,478
Get ahold of your stomach,
it's goin' into your butt!

1533
01:29:46,650 --> 01:29:49,346
Wooo!

1534
01:29:49,453 --> 01:29:51,250
Sister Cutbank!

1535
01:29:51,589 --> 01:29:52,988
I'm gonna be sick.

1536
01:29:53,090 --> 01:29:54,216
Sister Cutbank!

1537
01:29:54,325 --> 01:29:56,452
Hey, what's that boy?

1538
01:29:56,560 --> 01:29:58,084
He's turning a little green.

1539
01:29:58,195 --> 01:29:58,889
No!

1540
01:29:58,996 --> 01:30:01,487
Ha ha ha ha!

1541
01:30:02,633 --> 01:30:05,534
I'm finished.
I'm done, Sister Cutbank.

1542
01:30:05,636 --> 01:30:06,762
No more, please!

1543
01:30:06,870 --> 01:30:09,100
Ha hah haa!

1544
01:30:11,809 --> 01:30:13,606
Ahhhhh!
We oughta do this again!

1545
01:30:13,744 --> 01:30:15,507
(Love bites!)

